# Part 4: AI Integration

## Feature Name

**Skill Normalization & Explainability Engine**

---

## Problem It Solves

Students describe skills inconsistently (e.g., “JS”, “JavaScript”, “frontend dev”), making it difficult to compare and balance teams.

---

## Input

* Student skill descriptions (text)
* Instructor project description

---

## Output

* Structured skill categories (e.g., frontend, backend, ML)
* Skill weights
* Natural-language explanation of team assignments

---

## Where It Appears in UI

* Team Results Screen (explanation panel)
* Instructor Dashboard (team reasoning summaries)

---

## Module

* AI Processing Module

---

## Why This AI Feature is Valuable

* Improves consistency in data
* Enhances explainability
* Supports better decision-making without replacing human control

---

# Part 5: System Mapping

## UI → API → Database Mapping

### Login

* UI: Login Screen
* API: `POST /login`
* Database: Users

---

### Submit Student Profile

* UI: Student Dashboard
* API: `POST /students/profile`
* Database: StudentProfiles, AvailabilityMatrix

---

### Configure Constraints

* UI: Instructor Dashboard
* API: `PUT /courses/constraints`
* Database: Courses, Constraints

---

### Run Match

* UI: Instructor Dashboard
* API: `POST /matchruns`
* Database: MatchRuns

---

### Get Teams

* UI: Team Results Screen
* API: `GET /teams`
* Database: Teams

---

### Submit Check-in

* UI: Contribution Tracking Screen
* API: `POST /checkins`
* Database: CheckIns

---

# Part 6: Existing System Analysis

## Existing System: CATME (Comprehensive Assessment of Team Member Effectiveness)

---

## Key Features

* Team formation based on surveys
* Peer evaluation system
* Instructor tools for managing teams

---

## Limitations

* Limited explainability of team assignments
* Less flexibility in constraint customization
* Older UI/UX design
* Less integration with modern cloud systems

---

## Comparison with TeamMatch

| Feature            | CATME        | TeamMatch                                     |
| ------------------ | ------------ | --------------------------------------------- |
| Team Formation     | Survey-based | Deterministic optimization                    |
| Explainability     | Limited      | Fully explainable                             |
| Custom Constraints | Limited      | Highly customizable                           |
| UI/UX              | Traditional  | Modern web interface                          |
| AI Usage           | Minimal      | Skill normalization + explanations            |
| Architecture       | Monolithic   | Cloud-native (AWS serverless + microservices) |

---

## What Makes TeamMatch Better

* **Deterministic and reproducible results** (same input = same output)
* **Explainable system** (clear reasoning for assignments)
* **Modern cloud architecture** (scalable and efficient)
* **Better UI/UX** for both students and instructors
* **AI-assisted processing** without losing transparency

---

## Improvements Introduced

* Skill normalization using AI
* Real-time analytics dashboards
* Contribution tracking and monitoring
* Asynchronous processing with agent microservices

---

## Why TeamMatch is More Efficient and Modern

* Uses serverless architecture (AWS Lambda, SQS, ECS)
* Separates frontend, API, and compute layers
* Handles large workloads asynchronously
* Provides faster, scalable performance

---

# Conclusion

This design transforms TeamMatch from a conceptual system into a **real-world application architecture**, showing how users interact with the system, how modules communicate, and how AI enhances functionality without sacrificing transparency or control.
